Observation: Better support for reproduction, log file analysis,  multithreaded debugging, and backward-in-time debugging is  needed. While all of these concepts have been demonstrated in  research, scalable, real-world solutions are needed.

- ## #logability
##logability #Supportability #Operational #Quality #Value #Creation #Value #Drivers #ValueBased #Software #Engineering #Software #Engineering 
“We have very good debugging tools, to be  honest. One [improvement] could be a standardized way of  putting some more source level debugging information in the  logs” (Subject 8). The practical limitations of adding more  information to log files are obvious, “in an ideal world, you’d  have the stack trace for every line that was written to the log  because you never know what you’re going to need. But, of  course, there’s going to be a lot of overhead” (Subject 15).
